07/03/2003
IZMIR, Turkey -- Three Dutch batteries of Patriot ground-based air defence missile systems deployed in Diyarbakir, southeast Turkey are ready for use, according to a NATO official quoted Thursday (6 March) by the Anadolu Agency. NATO Allied Forces Southern Europe says Adm Gregory Johnson has assumed control of the batteries. The Patriots were deployed after NATO's Defence Planning Committee authorised assistance to Turkey. (Anadolu Agency - 06/03/03)
